Snake Game
A simple Snake game implemented in Java using Swing for the GUI. This project follows a Maven-based structure and runs as a standalone desktop application.

Features
Classic Snake gameplay

Grid-based movement

Food spawning & score tracking

"Game Over" & Restart functionality

Simple & clean UI

Project Structure
bash
Copy
Edit
Snake/
 ├── src/                       
 │   ├── main/                  
 │   │   ├── java/              
 │   │   │   └── org/example/   
 │   │   │       ├── Main.java        # Initializes JFrame and game  
 │   │   │       ├── SnakeGame.java   # Handles game logic  
 │   │   ├── resources/         # (Optional) Stores assets like images/sounds  
 │   ├── test/                  # Unit tests (currently empty)  
 ├── target/                    # Compiled files & JAR output (generated by Maven)  
 ├── .gitignore                 # Ignore unnecessary files  
 ├── pom.xml                    # Maven configuration  
 ├── README.md                  # Project documentation  
Installation & Running the Game
1. Clone the Repository
sh
Copy
Edit
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/SnakeGame.git
cd SnakeGame
2. Build & Run with Maven
If you have Maven installed, you can compile and run the project with:

sh
Copy
Edit
mvn clean package
java -jar target/SnakeGame.jar
3. Run Manually (Without Maven)
If you don’t use Maven, compile and run with:

sh
Copy
Edit
javac -d out src/main/java/org/example/*.java
java -cp out org.example.Main
Game Controls
Arrow Keys → Move the snake

Enter → Restart after Game Over


